-- ABB, Bayer, Enel, Fiat, Fluxys: European Equity Preview
-- B y   J o s e p h   C i o l l i
-- 2012-03-15T04:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-14/abb-bayer-enel-fiat-fluxys-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European (SXXP)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index (SXXP)  rose 0.3 percent to 270.27. The
 Stoxx 50 Index (SX5P)  increased 0.3 percent to 2,533.70. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro, gained
0.7 percent to 2,574.79.  ABB Ltd. (ABBN)  : The power technology company paid $10
million for convertible debt in Ecotality Inc. (ECTY US) and an
agreement to use its electric vehicle charging network. The
shares rose 1.2 percent to 19.17 Swiss francs.  Archos SA (JXR)  : The maker of tablet computers reported
2011 net income excluding some items of 5.7 million euros ($7.4
million), falling short of the average analyst estimate of 9.1
million euros. The shares gained 0.3 percent to 9.37 euros.  Bayer AG (BAYN)  (BAYN GY): The largest German drugmaker said that
the U.S.  Food and Drug Administration  approved a new indication
for oral contraceptive Natazia to treat heavy menstrual
bleeding. The shares fell 0.7 percent to 55.26 euros.  Enel SpA (ENEL)  :  Italy ’s biggest power company was cut
to sell from hold at Centrobanca SpA. The shares decreased 0.3
percent to 2.85 euros.  Fiat SpA (F)  : The Italian carmaker said a truckers’
strike that’s lasted 20 days has reduced production by 20,000
units and will reduce its market share by 10 percent in March.
The shares increased 2.5 percent to 4.82 euros.  Fluxys SA (FLUX)  : The manager of  Belgium ’s natural-gas
grid reported 2011 sales of 709.9 million euros, beating the
average estimate of 662.5 million euros by two analysts in a
Bloomberg survey. The company also said it will distribute 623.9
million euros to shareholders following a planned 100-for-1
stock split. The shares fell 2.7 percent to 3,205 euros.  Groupe Bruxelles Lambert SA (GBLB)  : The Belgian
investment firm controlled by billionaires  Albert Frere  and Paul
G. Desmarais is selling as many as 6.2 million shares of  Pernod-
Ricard SA (RI)   in a private placement. Groupe Bruxelles
gained 1 percent to 57.22 euros. Pernod-Ricard advanced 0.5
percent to 82.10 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joseph Ciolli in New York at 
